<section>

<h1>After Builders Cleaning Cost Guide</h1>

<p>
After renovation work is completed most properties require specialist
cleaning to remove plaster dust, installation residue and construction
contamination. The cost of after builders cleaning varies depending on the
size of the property, the scale of renovation work and the amount of
construction dust present.
</p>

</section>

<section>

<h2>Typical After Builders Cleaning Costs</h2>

<p>
Prices vary depending on property size and project intensity, but typical
ranges in the UK are:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Small apartment renovation clean: £120 – £220</li>
<li>2–3 bedroom property refurb clean: £180 – £350</li>
<li>Large renovation or extension clean: £300 – £600+</li>
</ul>

<p>
These ranges reflect the additional time required to remove fine plaster
dust and installation residue compared with standard domestic cleaning.
</p>

</section>

<section>

<h2>What Affects After Builders Cleaning Costs</h2>

<ul>
<li>Size of the property</li>
<li>Number of renovated rooms</li>
<li>Level of plaster and sanding dust</li>
<li>Kitchen or bathroom installation residue</li>
<li>Floor sanding projects</li>
<li>Access and parking conditions</li>
</ul>

</section>

<section>

<h2>Why Construction Dust Increases Cleaning Time</h2>

<p>
Fine plaster dust spreads easily throughout a property and often requires
multiple extraction passes before surfaces remain clear. High-level dust
removal, fixture detailing and repeated vacuuming increase labour time
compared with standard cleaning.
</p>

</section>

<section>

<h2>When After Builders Cleaning Is Required</h2>

<ul>
<li>Full property refurbishment</li>
<li>Kitchen installation</li>
<li>Bathroom renovation</li>
<li>Property extension projects</li>
<li>New build handover preparation</li>
</ul>

</section>

<section>

<h2>Professional After Builders Cleaning</h2>

<p>
Professional after builders cleaning removes construction dust and residue
after renovation projects and prepares the property for occupation or
inspection.
</p>

